<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/589: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-29T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                            1919, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your April 23, 11 a.m.</p>
                            <p>Report to Department any new developments in situation and intimate
                                to President Chamorro that the Department hopes that he will be
                                governed in his actions by the principles of international
                                comity.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>